52/* static */
53StatusOr<std::unique_ptr<HloInstruction>> HloInstruction::CreateFromProto(
54 HloModule* module, const HloInstructionProto& proto,
55 const tensorflow::gtl::FlatMap<int64, HloInstruction*>& instruction_map,
56 const tensorflow::gtl::FlatMap<int64, HloComputation*>& computation_map) {
57 TF_RET_CHECK(!proto.opcode().empty());
58 TF_ASSIGN_OR_RETURN(HloOpcode opcode, StringToHloOpcode(proto.opcode()));
59 TF_RET_CHECK(proto.has_shape());
60
61 auto instruction = WrapUnique(new HloInstruction(opcode, proto.shape()));
62 for (const int64 operand_id : proto.operand_ids()) {
63 TF_RET_CHECK(ContainsKey(instruction_map, operand_id))
64 << "No instruction with id " << operand_id;
65 instruction->AppendOperand(instruction_map.at(operand_id));
66 }
67 for (const int64 predecessor_id : proto.control_predecessor_ids()) {
68 TF_RET_CHECK(ContainsKey(instruction_map, predecessor_id))
69 << "No instruction with id " << predecessor_id;
70 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(instruction_map.at(predecessor_id)
71 ->AddControlDependencyTo(instruction.get()));
72 }
73
74 // In the proto, fused computations are held exclusively within the
75 // HloInstructionProto and do not appear as an HloComputationProto within the
76 // HloModuleProto.
77 if (instruction->opcode() == HloOpcode::kFusion) {
78 TF_RET_CHECK(!proto.fusion_kind().empty());
79 TF_ASSIGN_OR_RETURN(instruction->fusion_kind_,
80 StringToFusionKind(proto.fusion_kind()));
81
82 // Find the fused computation and set its fusion instruction.
83 TF_RET_CHECK(proto.called_computation_ids_size() == 1)
84 << "Expect 1 called computation for fusion instruction, but sees "
85 << proto.called_computation_ids_size();
86 const int64 fusion_id = proto.called_computation_ids(0);
87 auto* fused_computation = FindPtrOrNull(computation_map, fusion_id);
88 TF_RET_CHECK(fused_computation != nullptr)
89 << "No fusion computation with id " << fusion_id;
90 fused_computation->SetFusionInstruction(instruction.get());
91 instruction->called_computations_.push_back(fused_computation);
92 } else {
93 for (const int64 computation_id : proto.called_computation_ids()) {
94 TF_RET_CHECK(ContainsKey(computation_map, computation_id))
95 << "No computation with id " << computation_id;
96 instruction->called_computations_.push_back(
97 computation_map.at(computation_id));
98 }
99 }
100
101 if (instruction->opcode() == HloOpcode::kTrace) {
102 TF_RET_CHECK(instruction->operands().size() == 1)
103 << "Trace instruction should have 1 operand but sees "
104 << instruction->operands().size();
105 instruction->mutable_operand(0)->set_tracing(instruction.get());
106 }
107
108 TF_RET_CHECK(!proto.name().empty());
109 instruction->name_ = proto.name();
110
111 instruction->metadata_ = proto.metadata();
112 if (proto.has_literal()) {
113 TF_ASSIGN_OR_RETURN(instruction->literal_,
114 Literal::CreateFromProto(proto.literal()));
115 }
116 instruction->parameter_number_ = proto.parameter_number();
117
118 instruction->tuple_index_ = proto.tuple_index();
119 for (int64 dimension : proto.dimensions()) {
120 instruction->dimensions_.push_back(dimension);
121 }
122 if (proto.has_window()) {
123 instruction->window_ = MakeUnique<Window>(proto.window());
124 }
125 if (proto.has_convolution_dimension_numbers()) {
126 instruction->convolution_dimension_numbers_ =
127 MakeUnique<ConvolutionDimensionNumbers>(
128 proto.convolution_dimension_numbers());
129 }
130 if (proto.has_dot_dimension_numbers()) {
131 instruction->dot_dimension_numbers_ =
132 MakeUnique<DotDimensionNumbers>(proto.dot_dimension_numbers());
133 }
134 for (const HloInstructionProto::SliceDimensions& slice_dimensions :
135 proto.slice_dimensions()) {
136 instruction->slice_starts_.push_back(slice_dimensions.start());
137 instruction->slice_limits_.push_back(slice_dimensions.limit());
138 instruction->slice_strides_.push_back(slice_dimensions.stride());
139 }
140 instruction->exponent_bits_ = proto.exponent_bits();
141 instruction->mantissa_bits_ = proto.mantissa_bits();
142 for (int64 dynamic_slice_size : proto.dynamic_slice_sizes()) {
143 instruction->dynamic_slice_sizes_.push_back(dynamic_slice_size);
144 }
145 if (proto.has_padding_config()) {
146 instruction->padding_config_ =
147 MakeUnique<PaddingConfig>(proto.padding_config());
148 }
149 instruction->outfeed_config_ = proto.outfeed_config();
150 instruction->distribution_ = proto.distribution();
151 instruction->epsilon_ = proto.epsilon();
152 instruction->feature_index_ = proto.feature_index();
153 instruction->channel_id_ = proto.channel_id();
154 instruction->infeed_config_ = proto.infeed_config();
155 instruction->custom_call_target_ = proto.custom_call_target();
156 instruction->outfeed_shape_ = proto.outfeed_shape();
157 instruction->fft_type_ = proto.fft_type();
158 for (int64 fft_len : proto.fft_length()) {
159 instruction->fft_length_.push_back(fft_len);
160 }
161
162 return std::move(instruction);
163}

165/* static */ std::unique_ptr<HloInstruction> HloInstruction::CreateParameter(
166 int64 parameter_number, const Shape& shape, const string& name) {
167 auto instruction =
168 WrapUnique(new HloInstruction(HloOpcode::kParameter, shape));
169 instruction->parameter_number_ = parameter_number;
170 instruction->name_ = name;
171 return instruction;
172}

174/* static */ std::unique_ptr<HloInstruction> HloInstruction::CreateTrace(
175 const string& tag, HloInstruction* operand) {
176 auto instruction =
177 WrapUnique(new HloInstruction(HloOpcode::kTrace, ShapeUtil::MakeNil()));
178 instruction->operands_.push_back(operand);
179 instruction->literal_ = Literal::CreateR1U8(tag);
180 operand->set_tracing(instruction.get());
181 return instruction;
182}

215/* static */ std::unique_ptr<HloInstruction> HloInstruction::CreateNary(
216 const Shape& shape, HloOpcode opcode,
217 tensorflow::gtl::ArraySlice<HloInstruction*> operands) {
218 if (opcode == HloOpcode::kCopy) {
219 // It is impossible to copy an opaque shape, we don't know how big it is.
220 CHECK(!ShapeUtil::IsOpaque(shape));
221 }
222 auto instruction = WrapUnique(new HloInstruction(opcode, shape));
223 for (auto operand : operands) {
224 instruction->AppendOperand(operand);
225 }
226 return instruction;
227}
228
229/* static */ std::unique_ptr<HloInstruction> HloInstruction::CreateUnary(
230 const Shape& shape, HloOpcode opcode, HloInstruction* operand) {
231 // Only certain opcodes are supported with CreateUnary: opcodes of unary
232 // instructions with no auxiliary fields.
233 switch (opcode) {
234 case HloOpcode::kAbs:
235 case HloOpcode::kRoundNearestAfz:
236 case HloOpcode::kBitcast:
237 case HloOpcode::kCeil:
238 case HloOpcode::kCopy:
239 case HloOpcode::kCos:
240 case HloOpcode::kExp:
241 case HloOpcode::kFloor:
242 case HloOpcode::kImag:
243 case HloOpcode::kIsFinite:
244 case HloOpcode::kLog:
245 case HloOpcode::kNot:
246 case HloOpcode::kNegate:
247 case HloOpcode::kReal:
248 case HloOpcode::kSign:
249 case HloOpcode::kSin:
250 case HloOpcode::kSort:
251 case HloOpcode::kTanh:
252 break;
253 default:
254 LOG(FATAL) << "Invalid unary instruction opcode "
255 << HloOpcodeString(opcode);
256 }
257 return CreateNary(shape, opcode, {operand});
258}
259
260/* static */ std::unique_ptr<HloInstruction> HloInstruction::CreateBinary(
261 const Shape& shape, HloOpcode opcode, HloInstruction* lhs,
262 HloInstruction* rhs) {
263 // Only certain opcodes are supported with CreateBinary: opcodes of binary
264 // instructions with no auxiliary fields.
265 switch (opcode) {
266 case HloOpcode::kAdd:
267 case HloOpcode::kAtan2:
268 case HloOpcode::kDivide:
269 case HloOpcode::kComplex:
270 case HloOpcode::kDot:
271 case HloOpcode::kEq:
272 case HloOpcode::kGe:
273 case HloOpcode::kGt:
274 case HloOpcode::kLe:
275 case HloOpcode::kLt:
276 case HloOpcode::kMaximum:
277 case HloOpcode::kMinimum:
278 case HloOpcode::kMultiply:
279 case HloOpcode::kNe:
280 case HloOpcode::kPower:
281 case HloOpcode::kRemainder:
282 case HloOpcode::kSubtract:
283 case HloOpcode::kAnd:
284 case HloOpcode::kOr:
285 case HloOpcode::kShiftLeft:
286 case HloOpcode::kShiftRightArithmetic:
287 case HloOpcode::kShiftRightLogical:
288 break;
289 default:
290 LOG(FATAL) << "Invalid binary instruction opcode "
291 << HloOpcodeString(opcode);
292 }
293 return CreateNary(shape, opcode, {lhs, rhs});
294}

296/* static */ std::unique_ptr<HloInstruction> HloInstruction::CreateTernary(
297 const Shape& shape, HloOpcode opcode, HloInstruction* lhs,
298 HloInstruction* rhs, HloInstruction* ehs) {
299 // Only certain opcodes are supported with CreateTernary: opcodes of ternary
300 // instructions with no auxiliary fields.
301 switch (opcode) {
302 case (HloOpcode::kClamp):
303 case (HloOpcode::kSelect):
304 break;
305 default:
306 LOG(FATAL) << "Invalid ternary instruction opcode "
307 << HloOpcodeString(opcode);
308 }
309 return CreateNary(shape, opcode, {lhs, rhs, ehs});
310}

313 const Shape& shape, HloOpcode opcode,

319/* static */ std::unique_ptr<HloInstruction> HloInstruction::CreateMap(
320 const Shape& shape, tensorflow::gtl::ArraySlice<HloInstruction*> operands,
321 HloComputation* map_computation,
322 tensorflow::gtl::ArraySlice<HloInstruction*> static_operands) {
323 CHECK(static_operands.empty()) << "static_operands not yet supported";
324 auto instruction = WrapUnique(new HloInstruction(HloOpcode::kMap, shape));
325 for (auto operand : operands) {
326 instruction->AppendOperand(operand);
327 }
328 instruction->called_computations_.push_back(map_computation);
329 return instruction;
330}

332/* static */ std::unique_ptr<HloInstruction> HloInstruction::CreateConvolve(
333 const Shape& shape, HloInstruction* lhs, HloInstruction* rhs,
334 const Window& window,
335 const ConvolutionDimensionNumbers& dimension_numbers) {
336 auto instruction =
337 WrapUnique(new HloInstruction(HloOpcode::kConvolution, shape));
338 if (window_util::HasBaseDilation(window)) {
339 instruction->name_ = instruction->name() + "-base-dilated";
340 }
341 if (window_util::HasWindowDilation(window)) {
342 instruction->name_ = instruction->name() + "-window-dilated";
343 }
344 instruction->AppendOperand(lhs);
345 instruction->AppendOperand(rhs);
346 instruction->window_ = MakeUnique<Window>(window);
347 instruction->convolution_dimension_numbers_ =
348 MakeUnique<ConvolutionDimensionNumbers>(dimension_numbers);
349 return instruction;
350}

373/* static */ std::unique_ptr<HloInstruction> HloInstruction::CreateCanonicalDot(
374 const Shape& shape, HloInstruction* lhs, HloInstruction* rhs) {
375 CHECK_EQ(ShapeUtil::Rank(lhs->shape()), 2);
376 CHECK_EQ(ShapeUtil::Rank(rhs->shape()), 2);
377
378 auto instruction = WrapUnique(new HloInstruction(HloOpcode::kDot, shape));
379 instruction->AppendOperand(lhs);
380 instruction->AppendOperand(rhs);
381 instruction->dot_dimension_numbers_ = MakeUnique<DotDimensionNumbers>();
382 instruction->dot_dimension_numbers_->add_lhs_contracting_dimensions(1);
383 instruction->dot_dimension_numbers_->add_rhs_contracting_dimensions(0);
384 return instruction;
385}

414 const Shape& shape, HloInstruction* operand,
415 tensorflow::StringPiece outfeed_config) {
416 std::unique_ptr<HloInstruction> instruction =
417 WrapUnique(new HloInstruction(HloOpcode::kOutfeed, ShapeUtil::MakeNil()));
418 CHECK(ShapeUtil::Compatible(operand->shape(), shape))
419 << "Outfeed shape " << shape << " must be compatible with operand shape "

423 instruction->outfeed_shape_ = shape;
424 return instruction;

482/* static */ std::unique_ptr<HloInstruction> HloInstruction::CreateWhile(
483 const Shape& shape, HloComputation* condition, HloComputation* body,
484 HloInstruction* init) {
485 auto instruction = WrapUnique(new HloInstruction(HloOpcode::kWhile, shape));
486 instruction->AppendOperand(init);
487 // Body comes before condition computation in the vector.
488 instruction->called_computations_.push_back(body);
489 instruction->called_computations_.push_back(condition);
490 return instruction;
491}
492
493/* static */ std::unique_ptr<HloInstruction> HloInstruction::CreateConditional(
494 const Shape& shape, HloInstruction* pred,
495 HloInstruction* true_computation_arg, HloComputation* true_computation,
496 HloInstruction* false_computation_arg, HloComputation* false_computation) {
497 auto instruction =
498 WrapUnique(new HloInstruction(HloOpcode::kConditional, shape));
499 instruction->AppendOperand(pred);
500 instruction->AppendOperand(true_computation_arg);
501 instruction->AppendOperand(false_computation_arg);
502 // In called_computations_, the index of true_computation must be 0 and that
503 // of false computation must be 1, as defined by kTrueComputationIndex and
504 // kFalseComputationIndex.
505 instruction->called_computations_.push_back(true_computation);
506 instruction->called_computations_.push_back(false_computation);
507 return instruction;
508}

510/* static */ std::unique_ptr<HloInstruction> HloInstruction::CreateSlice(
511 const Shape& shape, HloInstruction* operand,
512 tensorflow::gtl::ArraySlice<int64> start_indices,
513 tensorflow::gtl::ArraySlice<int64> limit_indices,
514 tensorflow::gtl::ArraySlice<int64> strides) {
515 auto instruction = WrapUnique(new HloInstruction(HloOpcode::kSlice, shape));
516 instruction->AppendOperand(operand);
517 instruction->slice_starts_.assign(start_indices.begin(), start_indices.end());
518 instruction->slice_limits_.assign(limit_indices.begin(), limit_indices.end());
519 instruction->slice_strides_.assign(strides.begin(), strides.end());
520 // For backward compatibility with old serialized computations: if there are
521 // no strides, assume all strides are 1.
522 // TODO(b/63317920): remove this code.
523 if (instruction->slice_strides_.empty()) {
524 instruction->slice_strides_ = std::vector<int64>(start_indices.size(), 1LL);
525 }
526 return instruction;
527}

582/* static */ std::unique_ptr<HloInstruction> HloInstruction::CreateReduce(
583 const Shape& shape, HloInstruction* arg, HloInstruction* init_value,
584 tensorflow::gtl::ArraySlice<int64> dimensions_to_reduce,
585 HloComputation* reduce_computation) {
586 auto instruction = WrapUnique(new HloInstruction(HloOpcode::kReduce, shape));
587 instruction->AppendOperand(arg);
588 instruction->AppendOperand(init_value);
589 instruction->dimensions_.assign(dimensions_to_reduce.begin(),

695/* static */ std::unique_ptr<HloInstruction>
696HloInstruction::CreateBroadcastSequence(
697 const Shape& output_shape, HloInstruction* operand,
698 const std::function<HloInstruction*(std::unique_ptr<HloInstruction>)>&
699 adder) {
700 CHECK(ShapeUtil::IsScalar(operand->shape()) ||
701 ShapeUtil::Rank(operand->shape()) == ShapeUtil::Rank(output_shape));
702 Shape broadcast_shape = ShapeUtil::ChangeElementType(
703 output_shape, operand->shape().element_type());
704 // Do explicit broadcast for scalar.
705 if (ShapeUtil::IsScalar(operand->shape())) {
706 auto broadcast =
707 HloInstruction::CreateBroadcast(broadcast_shape, operand, {});
708 broadcast->set_metadata(operand->metadata());
709 if (operand->has_sharding()) {
710 broadcast->set_sharding(operand->sharding());
711 }
712 return broadcast;
713 }
714 // Do explicit broadcast for degenerate broadcast.
715 std::vector<int64> broadcast_dimensions;
716 std::vector<int64> reshaped_dimensions;
717 for (int i = 0; i < ShapeUtil::Rank(operand->shape()); i++) {
718 if (operand->shape().dimensions(i) == output_shape.dimensions(i)) {
719 broadcast_dimensions.push_back(i);
720 reshaped_dimensions.push_back(operand->shape().dimensions(i));
721 } else {
722 CHECK_EQ(operand->shape().dimensions(i), 1)
723 << "An explicit broadcast sequence requires the broadcasted "
724 "dimensions to be trivial; operand: "
725 << operand->ToString() << "; output_shape: " << output_shape;
726 }
727 }
728 // Eliminate the size one dimensions.
729 HloInstruction* reshaped_operand = adder(HloInstruction::CreateReshape(
730 ShapeUtil::MakeShape(operand->shape().element_type(),
731 reshaped_dimensions),
732 operand));
733 reshaped_operand->set_metadata(operand->metadata());
734 if (operand->has_sharding()) {
735 reshaped_operand->set_sharding(operand->sharding());
736 }
737 // Broadcast 'reshape' up to the larger size.
738 auto broadcast = HloInstruction::CreateBroadcast(
739 broadcast_shape, reshaped_operand, broadcast_dimensions);
740 broadcast->set_metadata(operand->metadata());
741 if (operand->has_sharding()) {
742 broadcast->set_sharding(operand->sharding());
743 }
744 return broadcast;
745}

824HloInstruction* HloInstruction::AddFusionOperand(HloInstruction* new_operand) {
825 CHECK_EQ(opcode(), HloOpcode::kFusion);
826 CHECK_EQ(operand_count(),
827 fused_instructions_computation()->parameter_instructions().size());
828 const int64 param_no = operand_count();
829 // Name the parameter after the instruction it represents in the outer
830 // (non-fusion) computation.
831 string param_name = StrCat(new_operand->name(), ".param_", param_no);
832 HloInstruction* fused_parameter =
833 fused_instructions_computation()->AddParameter(
834 HloInstruction::CreateParameter(param_no, new_operand->shape(),
835 param_name));
836 AppendOperand(new_operand);
837 return fused_parameter;
838}
839
840void HloInstruction::MergeFusionInstruction(
841 HloInstruction* instruction_to_merge) {
842 CHECK_EQ(opcode_, HloOpcode::kFusion);
843 CHECK_EQ(instruction_to_merge->opcode(), HloOpcode::kFusion);
844 CHECK(std::find(operands().begin(), operands().end(), instruction_to_merge) !=
845 operands().end());
846 // Clone the instruction from which to merge fused instructions.
847 std::unique_ptr<HloInstruction> clone = instruction_to_merge->Clone();
848 // Replace uses of fused parameters with the corresponding operand of the
849 // fusion. Add all non-parameter fused instructions to 'unfused_instructions'
850 // to be merged into 'this'. This is done in reverse post order.
851 std::vector<HloInstruction*> unfused_instructions;
852 auto fused_instructions =
853 clone->fused_instructions_computation()->MakeInstructionPostOrder();
854 for (auto fused_it = fused_instructions.rbegin();
855 fused_it != fused_instructions.rend(); ++fused_it) {
856 auto fused_instruction = *fused_it;
857 if (fused_instruction->opcode() == HloOpcode::kParameter) {
858 TF_CHECK_OK(fused_instruction->ReplaceAllUsesWith(
859 clone->mutable_operand(fused_instruction->parameter_number())));
860 } else {
861 unfused_instructions.push_back(fused_instruction);
862 }
863 }
864 CHECK(unfused_instructions.front() == clone->fused_expression_root());
865 // Replace instruction_to_merge use of 'this' with unfused_root.
866 TF_CHECK_OK(
867 instruction_to_merge->ReplaceUseWith(this, unfused_instructions.front()));
868 // Fuse 'unfused_instructions' into 'this'.
869 for (auto& instruction : unfused_instructions) {
870 FuseInstruction(instruction);
871 instruction->DetachFromOperands();
872 }
873 CHECK_EQ(0, clone->user_count());
874 clone->DetachFromOperands();
875 TF_CHECK_OK(parent()->parent()->RemoveEmbeddedComputation(
876 clone->fused_instructions_computation()));
877}
878
879void HloInstruction::MergeFusionInstructionIntoMultiOutput(
880 HloInstruction* instruction_to_merge) {
881 CHECK_EQ(opcode_, HloOpcode::kFusion);
882 CHECK_EQ(instruction_to_merge->opcode(), HloOpcode::kFusion);
883 // Add all non-parameter fused instructions to 'unfused_instructions' to be
884 // merged into 'this'. `old_to_new' maps the instructions in the fused node
885 // to the disaseembled fusion instructions.
886 // Note that we add the unfused instructions to this->parent_ computation.
887 // This is necessary because the unique_id needs for an instruction and
888 // it's only added when inserting to the computation.
889 tensorflow::gtl::FlatMap<HloInstruction*, HloInstruction*> old_to_new;
890 std::vector<HloInstruction*> unfused_instructions;
891 auto computation_to_merge =
892 instruction_to_merge->fused_instructions_computation();
893 auto post_order = computation_to_merge->MakeInstructionPostOrder();
894 for (auto rit = post_order.rbegin(); rit != post_order.rend(); ++rit) {
895 auto fused_instruction = *rit;
896 if (fused_instruction->opcode() == HloOpcode::kParameter) {
897 InsertOrDie(&old_to_new, fused_instruction,
898 instruction_to_merge->mutable_operand(
899 fused_instruction->parameter_number()));
900 continue;
901 }
902
903 // Here we clone the insertion and call FuseInstructionIntoMultiOutput()
904 // which clones again. This can be improved.
905 auto cloned_instruction =
906 parent_->AddInstruction(fused_instruction->Clone());
907 unfused_instructions.push_back(cloned_instruction);
908 InsertOrDie(&old_to_new, fused_instruction, cloned_instruction);
909 }
910 for (auto unfused_instruction : unfused_instructions) {
911 for (int64 index = 0; index < unfused_instruction->operand_count();
912 index++) {
913 auto new_operand =
914 FindOrDie(old_to_new, unfused_instruction->mutable_operand(index));
915 TF_CHECK_OK(unfused_instruction->ReplaceOperandWith(index, new_operand));
916 }
917 }
918
919 HloInstruction* unfused_root = unfused_instructions.front();
920 TF_CHECK_OK(instruction_to_merge->ReplaceAllUsesWith(unfused_root));
921
922 TF_CHECK_OK(
923 instruction_to_merge->parent()->RemoveInstruction(instruction_to_merge));
924 if (GetModule()) {
925 TF_CHECK_OK(GetModule()->RemoveEmbeddedComputation(computation_to_merge));
926 }
927
928 // Fuse the root instruction and generate multiple outputs.
929 FuseInstructionIntoMultiOutput(unfused_root);
930 TF_CHECK_OK(unfused_root->parent()->RemoveInstruction(unfused_root));
931 // The rest instructions are of normal fusing.
932 for (int64 i = 1; i < unfused_instructions.size(); i++) {
933 auto instruction = unfused_instructions[i];
934 FuseInstruction(instruction);
935 TF_CHECK_OK(instruction->parent()->RemoveInstruction(instruction));
936 }
937}
938
939HloInstruction* HloInstruction::FuseInstructionInternal(
940 HloInstruction* instruction_to_fuse, bool add_output) {
941 CHECK_EQ(opcode_, HloOpcode::kFusion);
942
943 // When add_output is false, this fusion instruction must be a user of
944 // instruction_to_fuse.
945 if (!add_output) {
946 CHECK(IsUserOf(instruction_to_fuse));
947 }
948 HloInstruction* fused_instruction =
949 CloneAndFuseInternal(instruction_to_fuse, add_output);
950 return fused_instruction;
951}
952
953HloInstruction* HloInstruction::CloneAndFuseInternal(
954 HloInstruction* instruction_to_fuse, bool add_output) {
955 CHECK_EQ(opcode_, HloOpcode::kFusion);
956 CHECK(instruction_to_fuse->IsFusable()) << instruction_to_fuse->ToString();
957 VLOG(3) << "CloneAndFuseInternal:\n" << instruction_to_fuse->ToString();
958 HloInstruction* clone = nullptr;
959 if (called_computations_.empty()) {
960 // New fusion instruction. It should not be a multioutput instruction.
961 CHECK(!add_output);
962 auto builder = HloComputation::Builder("fused_computation", this);
963 builder.AddInstruction(instruction_to_fuse->Clone(/*suffix=*/""));
964 called_computations_.push_back(
965 CHECK_NOTNULL(GetModule())->AddEmbeddedComputation(builder.Build()));
966 clone = fused_expression_root();
967 } else {
968 clone = fused_instructions_computation()->AddInstruction(
969 instruction_to_fuse->Clone(/*suffix=*/""));
970 // When add_output is false, instruction_to_fuse is necessarily an operand
971 // of the fusion instruction. After fusion this will no longer be the case.
972 // Remove the operand from the operand list and remove its corresponding
973 // fused parameter instruction. Renumber parameters as necessary to make
974 // parameter numbers consistent with their index in the
975 // fused_parameter_ vector.
976 bool in_operand_list = std::find(operands_.begin(), operands_.end(),
977 instruction_to_fuse) != operands_.end();
978 CHECK(add_output || in_operand_list);
979 const std::vector<HloInstruction*>& fused_parameters =
980 fused_instructions_computation()->parameter_instructions();
981 for (int64 operand_num = 0; operand_num < operand_count(); ++operand_num) {
982 if (instruction_to_fuse == operands_[operand_num]) {
983 // replace the fused parameter instruction's uses with the clone.
984 HloInstruction* fused_parameter = fused_parameters[operand_num];
985 TF_CHECK_OK(fused_parameter->ReplaceAllUsesWith(clone));
986
987 // Remove the corresponding fused parameter and operand from their
988 // respective vectors.
989 TF_CHECK_OK(
990 fused_instructions_computation()->RemoveParameter(operand_num));
991 operands_.erase(operands_.begin() + operand_num);
992 break;
993 }
994 }
995 // We've cloned instruction_to_fuse into this fusion instruction, so this
996 // fusion instruction is no longer a use of instruction_to_fuse.
997 if (in_operand_list) {
998 instruction_to_fuse->RemoveUser(this);
999 // When the instruction_to_fuse does not have other users, we don't need
1000 // to generate a multioutput fusion instruction.
1001 if (instruction_to_fuse->user_count() == 0) {
1002 add_output = false;
1003 }
1004 }
1005 }
1006
1007 // Reread the parameters in the computation.
1008 const std::vector<HloInstruction*>& fused_parameters =
1009 fused_instructions_computation()->parameter_instructions();
1010
1011 // Add each operand of the clone as an operand of the fusion instruction. A
1012 // complication is that some clone operands may already be operands of the
1013 // fusion instruction.
1014 for (int64 operand_num = 0; operand_num < clone->operand_count();
1015 ++operand_num) {
1016 HloInstruction* operand = clone->mutable_operand(operand_num);
1017
1018 // See if this operand is already an operand of the fusion node.
1019 CHECK_EQ(operands_.size(), fused_parameters.size());
1020 HloInstruction* fused_param = nullptr;
1021 for (int64 i = 0; i < operands_.size(); ++i) {
1022 if (operands_[i] == operand) {
1023 fused_param = fused_parameters[i];
1024 break;
1025 }
1026 }
1027
1028 if (fused_param == nullptr) {
1029 // Clone's operand was not already an operand of the fusion
1030 // instruction. Add it as an operand and add a corresponding fused
1031 // parameter instruction.
1032 fused_param = AddFusionOperand(operand);
1033 }
1034 TF_CHECK_OK(clone->ReplaceOperandWith(operand_num, fused_param));
1035 }
1036
1037 if (add_output) {
1038 CHECK_GT(instruction_to_fuse->user_count(), 0);
1039 // If this is already a multioutput fusion instruction, expand the root
1040 // tuple by 1.
1041 HloInstruction* fused_root = fused_expression_root();
1042 HloInstruction::InstructionVector tuple_elements;
1043 bool newly_created_tuple_instr = false;
1044 if (fused_root->opcode() == HloOpcode::kTuple) {
1045 tuple_elements = fused_root->operands();
1046 } else {
1047 tuple_elements.push_back(fused_root);
1048 newly_created_tuple_instr = true;
1049 }
1050 if (clone->opcode() == HloOpcode::kTuple) {
1051 for (auto inst : clone->operands()) {
1052 tuple_elements.push_back(inst);
1053 }
1054 } else {
1055 tuple_elements.push_back(clone);
1056 }
1057 HloInstruction* new_root = fused_instructions_computation()->AddInstruction(
1058 HloInstruction::CreateTuple(tuple_elements));
1059 fused_instructions_computation()->set_root_instruction(new_root);
1060 shape_ = new_root->shape();
1061 if (fused_root->opcode() == HloOpcode::kTuple) {
1062 TF_CHECK_OK(
1063 fused_instructions_computation()->RemoveInstruction(fused_root));
1064 }
1065
1066 // If this is a newly created multioutput instruction, we need to update
1067 // the use of the original fusion instruction.
1068 if (newly_created_tuple_instr) {
1069 HloInstruction* new_instr = parent_->AddInstruction(
1070 HloInstruction::CreateGetTupleElement(fused_root->shape(), this, 0));
1071 TF_CHECK_OK(ReplaceAllUsesWith(new_instr));
1072 }
1073 int64 index = tuple_elements.size();
1074 if (instruction_to_fuse->opcode() == HloOpcode::kTuple) {
1075 index -= instruction_to_fuse->operand_count();
1076 std::vector<HloInstruction*> to_be_removed;
1077 for (auto old_gte : instruction_to_fuse->users()) {
1078 CHECK_EQ(old_gte->opcode(), HloOpcode::kGetTupleElement);
1079 int64 old_tuple_index = old_gte->tuple_index();
1080 HloInstruction* new_gte =
1081 parent_->AddInstruction(HloInstruction::CreateGetTupleElement(
1082 old_gte->shape(), this, index + old_tuple_index));
1083 TF_CHECK_OK(old_gte->ReplaceAllUsesWith(new_gte));
1084 to_be_removed.push_back(old_gte);
1085 }
1086 for (auto old_gte : to_be_removed) {
1087 TF_CHECK_OK(parent_->RemoveInstruction(old_gte));
1088 }
1089 TF_CHECK_OK(fused_instructions_computation()->RemoveInstruction(clone));
1090 } else {
1091 HloInstruction* new_gte =
1092 parent_->AddInstruction(HloInstruction::CreateGetTupleElement(
1093 clone->shape(), this, index - 1));
1094 TF_CHECK_OK(instruction_to_fuse->ReplaceAllUsesWith(new_gte));
1095 }
1096 }
1097
1098 VLOG(2) << "New clone:\n" << clone->ToString();
1099 return clone;
1100}

1102RandomDistribution HloInstruction::random_distribution() const {
1103 CHECK_EQ(opcode_, HloOpcode::kRng);
1104 return distribution_;
1105}
1106
1107bool HloInstruction::HasSideEffect() const {
1108 switch (opcode_) {
1109 case HloOpcode::kSend:
1110 case HloOpcode::kSendDone:
1111 case HloOpcode::kRecv:
1112 case HloOpcode::kRecvDone:
1113 case HloOpcode::kRng:
1114 case HloOpcode::kInfeed:
1115 case HloOpcode::kOutfeed:
1116 case HloOpcode::kTrace:
1117 case HloOpcode::kHostCompute:
1118 return true;
1119 default: {
1120 // Check if any of the called computations has a side effect.
1121 for (const auto& computation : called_computations()) {
1122 if (computation->HasSideEffect()) {
1123 return true;
1124 }
1125 }
1126 return false;
1127 }
1128 }
1129}

1155/* static */ std::unique_ptr<HloInstruction> HloInstruction::CreateHostCompute(
1156 const Shape& shape, tensorflow::gtl::ArraySlice<HloInstruction*> operands,
1157 tensorflow::StringPiece channel_name, const int64 cost_estimate_ns) {
1158 std::unique_ptr<HloInstruction> instruction =
1159 WrapUnique(new HloInstruction(HloOpcode::kHostCompute, shape));
1160 for (auto operand : operands) {
1161 instruction->AppendOperand(operand);
1162 }
1163 instruction->channel_name_ = channel_name.ToString();
1164 instruction->cost_estimate_ns_ = cost_estimate_ns;
1165 return instruction;
1166}

1168/* static */ std::unique_ptr<HloInstruction> HloInstruction::CreateTuple(
1169 tensorflow::gtl::ArraySlice<HloInstruction*> elements) {
1170 std::vector<Shape> element_shapes;
1171 for (auto element : elements) {
1172 element_shapes.push_back(element->shape());
1173 }
1174 Shape tuple_shape = ShapeUtil::MakeTupleShape(element_shapes);
1175 return CreateVariadic(tuple_shape, HloOpcode::kTuple, elements);
1176}
1177
1178/* static */ std::unique_ptr<HloInstruction> HloInstruction::CreateGather(
1179 const Shape& shape, HloInstruction* operand, HloInstruction* gather_indices,
1180 const GatherDimensionNumbers& gather_dim_numbers,
1181 tensorflow::gtl::ArraySlice<int64> window_bounds) {
1182 std::unique_ptr<HloInstruction> instruction =
1183 WrapUnique(new HloInstruction(HloOpcode::kGather, shape));
1184 instruction->AppendOperand(operand);
1185 instruction->AppendOperand(gather_indices);
1186 instruction->gather_dimension_numbers_ =
1187 MakeUnique<GatherDimensionNumbers>(gather_dim_numbers);
1188 c_copy(window_bounds, std::back_inserter(instruction->gather_window_bounds_));
1189 return instruction;
1190}
1191
1192/* static */ GatherDimensionNumbers HloInstruction::MakeGatherDimNumbers(
1193 tensorflow::gtl::ArraySlice<int64> output_window_dims,
1194 tensorflow::gtl::ArraySlice<int64> elided_window_dims,
1195 tensorflow::gtl::ArraySlice<int64> gather_dims_to_operand_dims,
1196 int64 index_vector_dim) {
1197 GatherDimensionNumbers gather_dim_numbers;
1198 for (int64 output_window_dim : output_window_dims) {
1199 gather_dim_numbers.add_output_window_dims(output_window_dim);
1200 }
1201 for (int64 elided_window_dim : elided_window_dims) {
1202 gather_dim_numbers.add_elided_window_dims(elided_window_dim);
1203 }
1204 for (int64 gather_dim_to_input_dim : gather_dims_to_operand_dims) {
1205 gather_dim_numbers.add_gather_dims_to_operand_dims(gather_dim_to_input_dim);
1206 }
1207
1208 gather_dim_numbers.set_index_vector_dim(index_vector_dim);
1209 return gather_dim_numbers;
1210}
1211
1212std::unique_ptr<HloInstruction> HloInstruction::CloneWithNewOperands(
1213 const Shape& shape,
1214 tensorflow::gtl::ArraySlice<HloInstruction*> new_operands,
1215 HloModule* module) const {
1216 VLOG(3) << "CloneWithNewOperands:\n " << ToString();
1217 VLOG(3) << " new operands:";
1218 for (const HloInstruction* new_operand : new_operands) {
1219 VLOG(3) << " %" << new_operand->name();
1220 }
1221
1222 std::unique_ptr<HloInstruction> clone;
1223
1224 // Explicitly call the factory for the instruction type. This is more robust
1225 // in the face of code changes than copying fields explicitly. This also
1226 // properly sets the user fields of the operands.
1227 switch (opcode_) {
1228 // Unary ops.
1229 case HloOpcode::kAbs:
1230 case HloOpcode::kRoundNearestAfz:
1231 case HloOpcode::kBitcast:
1232 case HloOpcode::kCeil:
1233 case HloOpcode::kCopy:
1234 case HloOpcode::kCos:
1235 case HloOpcode::kExp:
1236 case HloOpcode::kImag:
1237 case HloOpcode::kIsFinite:
1238 case HloOpcode::kFloor:
1239 case HloOpcode::kLog:
1240 case HloOpcode::kNot:
1241 case HloOpcode::kNegate:
1242 case HloOpcode::kReal:
1243 case HloOpcode::kSign:
1244 case HloOpcode::kSin:
1245 case HloOpcode::kSort:
1246 case HloOpcode::kTanh:
1247 CHECK_EQ(new_operands.size(), 1);
1248 clone = CreateUnary(shape, opcode_, new_operands[0]);
1249 break;
1250 // Binary ops.
1251 case HloOpcode::kAdd:
1252 case HloOpcode::kAtan2:
1253 case HloOpcode::kComplex:
1254 case HloOpcode::kDivide:
1255 case HloOpcode::kMultiply:
1256 case HloOpcode::kSubtract:
1257 case HloOpcode::kEq:
1258 case HloOpcode::kGe:
1259 case HloOpcode::kGt:
1260 case HloOpcode::kLe:
1261 case HloOpcode::kLt:
1262 case HloOpcode::kNe:
1263 case HloOpcode::kMaximum:
1264 case HloOpcode::kMinimum:
1265 case HloOpcode::kPower:
1266 case HloOpcode::kRemainder:
1267 case HloOpcode::kAnd:
1268 case HloOpcode::kOr:
1269 case HloOpcode::kShiftLeft:
1270 case HloOpcode::kShiftRightArithmetic:
1271 case HloOpcode::kShiftRightLogical:
1272 CHECK_EQ(new_operands.size(), 2);
1273 clone = CreateBinary(shape, opcode_, new_operands[0], new_operands[1]);
1274 break;
1275 // Ternary ops.
1276 case HloOpcode::kClamp:
1277 case HloOpcode::kSelect:
1278 CHECK_EQ(new_operands.size(), 3);
1279 clone = CreateTernary(shape, opcode_, new_operands[0], new_operands[1],
1280 new_operands[2]);
1281 break;
1282 // Other supported ops.
1283 case HloOpcode::kBroadcast:
1284 CHECK_EQ(new_operands.size(), 1);
1285 clone = CreateBroadcast(shape, new_operands[0], dimensions_);
1286 break;
1287 case HloOpcode::kBroadcastDimOne:
1288 CHECK_EQ(new_operands.size(), 1);
1289 clone = CreateBroadcastDimOne(shape, new_operands[0]);
1290 break;
1291 case HloOpcode::kCall:
1292 clone = CreateCall(shape, new_operands, to_apply());
1293 break;
1294 case HloOpcode::kCustomCall:
1295 clone = CreateCustomCall(shape, new_operands, custom_call_target_);
1296 break;
1297 case HloOpcode::kHostCompute:
1298 clone = CreateHostCompute(shape, new_operands, channel_name_,
1299 cost_estimate_ns_);
1300 break;
1301 case HloOpcode::kConcatenate:
1302 clone = CreateConcatenate(shape, new_operands, dimensions(0));
1303 break;
1304 case HloOpcode::kConvert:
1305 CHECK_EQ(new_operands.size(), 1);
1306 clone = CreateConvert(shape, new_operands[0]);
1307 break;
1308 case HloOpcode::kBitcastConvert:
1309 CHECK_EQ(new_operands.size(), 1);
1310 clone = CreateBitcastConvert(shape, new_operands[0]);
1311 break;
1312 case HloOpcode::kReducePrecision:
1313 CHECK_EQ(new_operands.size(), 1);
1314 clone = CreateReducePrecision(shape, new_operands[0], exponent_bits_,
1315 mantissa_bits_);
1316 break;
1317 case HloOpcode::kConvolution:
1318 CHECK_EQ(new_operands.size(), 2);
1319 clone = CreateConvolve(shape, new_operands[0], new_operands[1], *window_,
1320 *convolution_dimension_numbers_);
1321 break;
1322 case HloOpcode::kDot:
1323 CHECK_EQ(new_operands.size(), 2);
1324 clone = CreateDot(shape, new_operands[0], new_operands[1],
1325 *dot_dimension_numbers_);
1326 break;
1327 case HloOpcode::kFft:
1328 CHECK_EQ(new_operands.size(), 1);
1329 return CreateFft(shape, new_operands[0], fft_type_, fft_length_);
1330 case HloOpcode::kCrossReplicaSum:
1331 clone = CreateCrossReplicaSum(shape, new_operands);
1332 break;
1333 case HloOpcode::kGetTupleElement:
1334 CHECK_EQ(new_operands.size(), 1);
1335 clone = CreateGetTupleElement(shape, new_operands[0], tuple_index());
1336 break;
1337 case HloOpcode::kMap:
1338 clone = CreateMap(shape, new_operands, to_apply());
1339 break;
1340 case HloOpcode::kPad:
1341 CHECK_EQ(new_operands.size(), 2);
1342 clone =
1343 CreatePad(shape, new_operands[0], new_operands[1], *padding_config_);
1344 break;
1345 case HloOpcode::kReduce:
1346 CHECK_EQ(new_operands.size(), 2);
1347 clone = CreateReduce(shape, new_operands[0], new_operands[1], dimensions_,
1348 to_apply());
1349 break;
1350 case HloOpcode::kReduceWindow:
1351 CHECK_EQ(new_operands.size(), 2);
1352 clone = CreateReduceWindow(shape, new_operands[0], new_operands[1],
1353 *window_, to_apply());
1354 break;
1355 case HloOpcode::kSelectAndScatter:
1356 CHECK_EQ(new_operands.size(), 3);
1357 clone =
1358 CreateSelectAndScatter(shape, new_operands[0], select(), *window_,
1359 new_operands[1], new_operands[2], scatter());
1360 break;
1361 case HloOpcode::kReverse:
1362 CHECK_EQ(new_operands.size(), 1);
1363 clone = CreateReverse(shape, new_operands[0], dimensions_);
1364 break;
1365 case HloOpcode::kRng:
1366 clone = CreateRng(shape, distribution_, new_operands);
1367 break;
1368 case HloOpcode::kReshape:
1369 CHECK_EQ(new_operands.size(), 1);
1370 clone = CreateReshape(shape, new_operands[0]);
1371 break;
1372 case HloOpcode::kSlice:
1373 CHECK_EQ(new_operands.size(), 1);
1374 clone = CreateSlice(shape, new_operands[0], slice_starts_, slice_limits_,
1375 slice_strides_);
1376 break;
1377 case HloOpcode::kDynamicSlice:
1378 clone = CreateDynamicSlice(shape, new_operands[0], new_operands[1],
1379 dynamic_slice_sizes_);
1380 break;
1381 case HloOpcode::kDynamicUpdateSlice:
1382 CHECK_EQ(new_operands.size(), 3);
1383 clone = CreateDynamicUpdateSlice(shape, new_operands[0], new_operands[1],
1384 new_operands[2]);
1385 break;
1386 case HloOpcode::kTranspose:
1387 CHECK_EQ(new_operands.size(), 1);
1388 clone = CreateTranspose(shape, new_operands[0], dimensions_);
1389 break;
1390 case HloOpcode::kTuple:
1391 clone = CreateTuple(new_operands);
1392 *clone->mutable_shape() = shape;
1393 break;
1394 case HloOpcode::kWhile:
1395 CHECK_EQ(new_operands.size(), 1);
1396 clone =
1397 CreateWhile(shape, while_condition(), while_body(), new_operands[0]);
1398 break;
1399 case HloOpcode::kConstant:
1400 clone = CreateConstant(literal_->CloneToUnique());
1401 break;
1402 case HloOpcode::kFusion:
1403 clone = CloneFusionWithNewOperands(shape, new_operands, module);
1404 break;
1405 case HloOpcode::kParameter:
1406 clone = CreateParameter(parameter_number_, shape, name_);
1407 break;
1408 case HloOpcode::kBatchNormTraining:
1409 CHECK_EQ(new_operands.size(), 3);
1410 clone =
1411 CreateBatchNormTraining(shape, new_operands[0], new_operands[1],
1412 new_operands[2], epsilon(), feature_index());
1413 break;
1414 case HloOpcode::kBatchNormInference:
1415 CHECK_EQ(new_operands.size(), 5);
1416 clone = CreateBatchNormInference(
1417 shape, new_operands[0], new_operands[1], new_operands[2],
1418 new_operands[3], new_operands[4], epsilon(), feature_index());
1419 break;
1420 case HloOpcode::kInfeed:
1421 CHECK_EQ(new_operands.size(), 0);
1422 clone = CreateInfeed(shape, infeed_config());
1423 break;
1424 case HloOpcode::kOutfeed:
1425 CHECK_EQ(new_operands.size(), 1);
1426 clone = CreateOutfeed(outfeed_shape_, new_operands[0], outfeed_config());
1427 break;
1428 case HloOpcode::kBatchNormGrad:
1429 CHECK_EQ(new_operands.size(), 5);
1430 clone = CreateBatchNormGrad(shape, new_operands[0], new_operands[1],
1431 new_operands[2], new_operands[3],
1432 new_operands[4], epsilon(), feature_index());
1433 break;
1434 case HloOpcode::kConditional:
1435 CHECK_EQ(new_operands.size(), 3);
1436 clone = CreateConditional(shape, new_operands[0], new_operands[1],
1437 true_computation(), new_operands[2],
1438 false_computation());
1439 break;
1440 case HloOpcode::kSend:
1441 CHECK_EQ(new_operands.size(), 1);
1442 clone = CreateSend(new_operands[0], channel_id());
1443 break;
1444 case HloOpcode::kSendDone:
1445 CHECK_EQ(new_operands.size(), 1);
1446 clone = CreateSendDone(new_operands[0]);
1447 break;
1448 case HloOpcode::kRecv:
1449 CHECK_EQ(new_operands.size(), 0);
1450 // The shape is a tuple, but CreateRecv() wants the raw data shape.
1451 clone =
1452 CreateRecv(ShapeUtil::GetTupleElementShape(shape, 0), channel_id());
1453 break;
1454 case HloOpcode::kRecvDone:
1455 CHECK_EQ(new_operands.size(), 1);
1456 clone = CreateRecvDone(new_operands[0]);
1457 break;
1458 case HloOpcode::kGather:
1459 CHECK_EQ(new_operands.size(), 2);
1460 clone = CreateGather(shape, new_operands[0], new_operands[1],
1461 *gather_dimension_numbers_, gather_window_bounds_);
1462 break;
1463 case HloOpcode::kTrace:
1464 LOG(FATAL) << "Not yet implemented, clone: " << HloOpcodeString(opcode_);
1465 }
1466 clone->set_metadata(metadata_);
1467 if (has_sharding()) {
1468 clone->set_sharding(sharding());
1469 }
1470 clone->set_parent(parent_);
1471 return clone;
1472}
1473
1474HloInstruction::~HloInstruction() {}
1475
1476std::unique_ptr<HloInstruction> HloInstruction::Clone(const string& suffix,
1477 HloModule* module) const {
1478 std::unique_ptr<HloInstruction> clone =
1479 CloneWithNewOperands(shape_, operands_, module);
1480 if (suffix.empty()) {
1481 clone->name_ = name();
1482 } else {
1483 // If an instruction is cloned multiple times avoid names like
1484 // foo.suffix.suffix.suffix. Instead of repeating the suffix add a numeric
1485 // suffix. Specifically, the clone of foo.suffix is named foo.suffix2, the
1486 // clone of foo.suffix2 is named foo.suffix3 and so on.
1487 const string dot_suffix = "." + suffix;
1488 size_t index = name().rfind(dot_suffix);
1489 if (index == string::npos) {
1490 // Existing name does not include ".suffix".
1491 clone->name_ = name() + dot_suffix;
1492 } else {
1493 // Existing name includes ".suffix". Determine if substring after
1494 // ".suffix" is numeric and should be replaced with an incremented number.
1495 string after_suffix = name().substr(index + dot_suffix.size());
1496 if (after_suffix.empty()) {
1497 // Existing name ends in ".suffix". New name should end in ".suffix2".
1498 clone->name_ = name() + "2";
1499 } else {
1500 // If names ends with .suffix[0-9]+ then replace with a suffix with the
1501 // numeric value incremented.
1502 int64 numeric_suffix;
1503 if (tensorflow::strings::safe_strto64(after_suffix, &numeric_suffix)) {
1504 clone->name_ =
1505 StrCat(name().substr(0, index), dot_suffix, numeric_suffix + 1);
1506 } else {
1507 // Substring after ".suffix" is non-numeric.
1508 clone->name_ = name() + dot_suffix;
1509 }
1510 }
1511 }
1512 }
1513 return clone;
1514}
1515
1516std::unique_ptr<HloInstruction> HloInstruction::CloneFusionWithNewOperands(
1517 const Shape& shape, tensorflow::gtl::ArraySlice<HloInstruction*> operands,
1518 HloModule* module) const {
1519 CHECK_EQ(opcode_, HloOpcode::kFusion);
1520 CHECK(parent() != nullptr);
1521
1522 auto new_instruction =
1523 WrapUnique(new HloInstruction(HloOpcode::kFusion, shape));
1524 // Add the operands to our new fusion instruction.
1525 for (HloInstruction* new_operand : operands) {
1526 new_instruction->AppendOperand(new_operand);
1527 }
1528 // Clone all the fused instructions for the new fusion instruction.
1529 HloInstructionMap<HloInstruction*> old_to_new;
1530 std::list<std::unique_ptr<HloInstruction>> new_fused_instructions;
1531 // Create the list of fused parameters by mapping through the cloned,
1532 // fused instructions.
1533 for (HloInstruction* old_fused_parameter :
1534 fused_instructions_computation()->parameter_instructions()) {
1535 new_fused_instructions.push_back(
1536 old_fused_parameter->Clone("clone", module));
1537 HloInstruction* new_fusion_parameter = new_fused_instructions.back().get();
1538 InsertOrDie(&old_to_new, old_fused_parameter, new_fusion_parameter);
1539 }
1540 for (auto old_fused_instruction :
1541 fused_instructions_computation()->MakeInstructionPostOrder()) {
1542 if (old_fused_instruction->opcode() == HloOpcode::kParameter) {
1543 FindOrDie(old_to_new, old_fused_instruction);
1544 continue;
1545 }
1546 std::vector<HloInstruction*> new_operands;
1547 for (int64 operand_idx = 0;
1548 operand_idx < old_fused_instruction->operand_count(); ++operand_idx) {
1549 HloInstruction* old_operand =
1550 old_fused_instruction->mutable_operand(operand_idx);
1551 new_operands.push_back(FindOrDie(old_to_new, old_operand));
1552 }
1553 new_fused_instructions.push_back(
1554 old_fused_instruction->CloneWithNewOperands(
1555 old_fused_instruction->shape(), new_operands, module));
1556 HloInstruction* new_fused_instruction = new_fused_instructions.back().get();
1557 new_fused_instruction->set_parent(parent_);
1558 InsertOrDie(&old_to_new, old_fused_instruction, new_fused_instruction);
1559 }
1560 new_instruction->fusion_kind_ = fusion_kind_;
1561 auto computation_builder = HloComputation::Builder(
1562 fused_instructions_computation()->name() + ".clone",
1563 new_instruction.get());
1564 // We iterated the fusion instructions in reverse post order which means
1565 // that we must reverse our new list of fusion instructions.
1566 for (auto new_fused_instruction_iter = new_fused_instructions.rbegin();
1567 new_fused_instruction_iter != new_fused_instructions.rend();
1568 ++new_fused_instruction_iter) {
1569 computation_builder.AddInstruction(std::move(*new_fused_instruction_iter));
1570 }
1571 if (module == nullptr) {
1572 module = GetModule();
1573 }
1574 auto fused_root_ = fused_expression_root();
1575 new_instruction->called_computations_.push_back(
1576 CHECK_NOTNULL(module)->AddEmbeddedComputation(
1577 computation_builder.Build(FindOrDie(old_to_new, fused_root_))));
1578 return new_instruction;
1579}
1580
1581std::pair<const HloInstruction*, ShapeIndex>
1582HloInstruction::LatestNonGteAncestorAndIndex() const {
1583 const HloInstruction* hlo = this;
1584 ShapeIndex index;
1585 while (hlo->opcode() == HloOpcode::kGetTupleElement) {
1586 index.push_back(hlo->tuple_index());
1587 hlo = hlo->operand(0);
1588 }
1589
1590 // We built up index in the reverse order from what we want.
1591 std::reverse(index.begin(), index.end());
1592
1593 return {hlo, index};
1594}
1595
1596const HloInstruction* HloInstruction::LatestNonGteAncestor() const {
1597 const HloInstruction* hlo = this;
1598 while (hlo->opcode() == HloOpcode::kGetTupleElement) {
1599 hlo = hlo->operand(0);
1600 }
1601 return hlo;
1602}

1653
1654Status HloInstruction::AddControlDependencyTo(HloInstruction* instruction) {
1655 TF_RET_CHECK(instruction->parent() == parent());
1656 if (std::find(control_successors_.begin(), control_successors_.end(),
1657 instruction) == control_successors_.end()) {
1658 control_successors_.push_back(instruction);
1659 TF_RET_CHECK(std::find(instruction->control_predecessors_.begin(),
1660 instruction->control_predecessors_.end(),
1661 this) == instruction->control_predecessors_.end());
1662 instruction->control_predecessors_.push_back(this);
1663 }
1664 return Status::OK();
1665}
1666
1667Status HloInstruction::RemoveControlDependencyTo(HloInstruction* instruction) {
1668 auto succ_it = std::find(control_successors_.begin(),
1669 control_successors_.end(), instruction);
1670 TF_RET_CHECK(succ_it != control_successors_.end());
1671 control_successors_.erase(succ_it);
1672 auto pred_it = std::find(instruction->control_predecessors_.begin(),
1673 instruction->control_predecessors_.end(), this);
1674 TF_RET_CHECK(pred_it != instruction->control_predecessors_.end());
1675 instruction->control_predecessors_.erase(pred_it);
1676
1677 return Status::OK();
1678}

1704
1705bool HloInstruction::IdenticalSlowPath(
1706 const HloInstruction& other,
1707 const std::function<bool(const HloComputation*, const HloComputation*)>&
1708 eq_computations,
1709 const std::function<bool(const Shape&, const Shape&)>& eq_shapes) const {
1710 // Perform opcode specific checks.
1711 switch (opcode()) {
1712 // The result of these instructions only depend upon their opcode and
1713 // operands.
1714 case HloOpcode::kAbs:
1715 case HloOpcode::kAtan2:
1716 case HloOpcode::kRoundNearestAfz:
1717 case HloOpcode::kAdd:
1718 case HloOpcode::kCeil:
1719 case HloOpcode::kClamp:
1720 case HloOpcode::kComplex:
1721 case HloOpcode::kCopy:
1722 case HloOpcode::kCos:
1723 case HloOpcode::kCrossReplicaSum:
1724 case HloOpcode::kDivide:
1725 case HloOpcode::kEq:
1726 case HloOpcode::kExp:
1727 case HloOpcode::kFloor:
1728 case HloOpcode::kGe:
1729 case HloOpcode::kGt:
1730 case HloOpcode::kImag:
1731 case HloOpcode::kIsFinite:
1732 case HloOpcode::kLe:
1733 case HloOpcode::kLog:
1734 case HloOpcode::kAnd:
1735 case HloOpcode::kNot:
1736 case HloOpcode::kOr:
1737 case HloOpcode::kLt:
1738 case HloOpcode::kMaximum:
1739 case HloOpcode::kMinimum:
1740 case HloOpcode::kMultiply:
1741 case HloOpcode::kNe:
1742 case HloOpcode::kNegate:
1743 case HloOpcode::kPower:
1744 case HloOpcode::kReal:
1745 case HloOpcode::kRemainder:
1746 case HloOpcode::kSelect:
1747 case HloOpcode::kShiftLeft:
1748 case HloOpcode::kShiftRightArithmetic:
1749 case HloOpcode::kShiftRightLogical:
1750 case HloOpcode::kSign:
1751 case HloOpcode::kSin:
1752 case HloOpcode::kSubtract:
1753 case HloOpcode::kTanh:
1754 case HloOpcode::kTuple:
1755 return true;
1756
1757 case HloOpcode::kFusion:
1758 return fusion_kind() == other.fusion_kind() &&
1759 eq_computations(fused_instructions_computation(),
1760 other.fused_instructions_computation());
1761
1762 // These opcodes have complex or special behavior so just return false.
1763 case HloOpcode::kRng:
1764 case HloOpcode::kTrace:
1765 case HloOpcode::kWhile:
1766 return false;
1767
1768 case HloOpcode::kParameter:
1769 return parameter_number() == other.parameter_number() &&
1770 // Check the shape too because `this` and `other` may be in
1771 // different HloComputations.
1772 eq_shapes(shape(), other.shape());
1773
1774 case HloOpcode::kBatchNormTraining:
1775 case HloOpcode::kBatchNormInference:
1776 case HloOpcode::kBatchNormGrad:
1777 return feature_index() == other.feature_index() &&
1778 epsilon() == other.epsilon();
1779
1780 // A constant is defined by the value in the literal.
1781 case HloOpcode::kConstant:
1782 return literal() == other.literal();
1783
1784 // A convert result is determined by the primitive type that the operand is
1785 // converted into.
1786 case HloOpcode::kConvert:
1787 case HloOpcode::kBitcastConvert:
1788 return shape().element_type() == other.shape().element_type();
1789
1790 // A reduce-precision operation is determined by the bit sizes.
1791 case HloOpcode::kReducePrecision:
1792 return exponent_bits() == other.exponent_bits() &&
1793 mantissa_bits() == other.mantissa_bits();
1794
1795 // Convolution has a window and dimensions.
1796 case HloOpcode::kConvolution:
1797 return protobuf_util::ProtobufEquals(window(), other.window()) &&
1798 protobuf_util::ProtobufEquals(
1799 convolution_dimension_numbers(),
1800 other.convolution_dimension_numbers());
1801 // Check dot dimension numbers.
1802 case HloOpcode::kDot:
1803 return protobuf_util::ProtobufEquals(dot_dimension_numbers(),
1804 other.dot_dimension_numbers());
1805
1806 case HloOpcode::kGather:
1807 return protobuf_util::ProtobufEquals(gather_dimension_numbers(),
1808 other.gather_dimension_numbers()) &&
1809 gather_window_bounds() == other.gather_window_bounds();
1810
1811 // FFT has various types & lengths.
1812 case HloOpcode::kFft:
1813 return fft_type() == other.fft_type() &&
1814 fft_length() == other.fft_length();
1815
1816 // Reduction results are determined by the reduction dimension and the
1817 // reduction computation.
1818 case HloOpcode::kReduce:
1819 return dimensions() == other.dimensions() &&
1820 eq_computations(to_apply(), other.to_apply());
1821 case HloOpcode::kReduceWindow:
1822 return eq_computations(to_apply(), other.to_apply()) &&
1823 protobuf_util::ProtobufEquals(window(), other.window());
1824
1825 // SelectAndScatter is determined by both select and scatter
1826 // computation as well as the window configuration.
1827 case HloOpcode::kSelectAndScatter:
1828 return eq_computations(select(), other.select()) &&
1829 eq_computations(scatter(), other.scatter()) &&
1830 protobuf_util::ProtobufEquals(window(), other.window());
1831
1832 case HloOpcode::kReshape:
1833 return eq_shapes(shape(), other.shape());
1834
1835 // Transpose result is determined by the final shape and the permutation.
1836 case HloOpcode::kTranspose:
1837 return eq_shapes(shape(), other.shape()) &&
1838 dimensions() == other.dimensions();
1839
1840 // Remaining instructions with special values.
1841 case HloOpcode::kBitcast:
1842 case HloOpcode::kBroadcastDimOne:
1843 case HloOpcode::kDynamicUpdateSlice:
1844 return eq_shapes(shape(), other.shape());
1845 case HloOpcode::kBroadcast:
1846 return eq_shapes(shape(), other.shape()) &&
1847 dimensions() == other.dimensions();
1848 case HloOpcode::kConcatenate:
1849 return dimensions() == other.dimensions();
1850 case HloOpcode::kGetTupleElement:
1851 return tuple_index() == other.tuple_index();
1852 case HloOpcode::kPad:
1853 return protobuf_util::ProtobufEquals(padding_config(),
1854 other.padding_config());
1855 case HloOpcode::kSlice:
1856 return slice_starts_ == other.slice_starts_ &&
1857 slice_limits_ == other.slice_limits_ &&
1858 slice_strides_ == other.slice_strides_;
1859 case HloOpcode::kDynamicSlice:
1860 return eq_shapes(shape(), other.shape()) &&
1861 dynamic_slice_sizes_ == other.dynamic_slice_sizes_;
1862 case HloOpcode::kCall:
1863 case HloOpcode::kMap:
1864 return eq_computations(to_apply(), other.to_apply());
1865 case HloOpcode::kCustomCall:
1866 return custom_call_target_ == other.custom_call_target_;
1867 case HloOpcode::kReverse:
1868 return dimensions() == other.dimensions();
1869 case HloOpcode::kConditional:
1870 return eq_computations(true_computation(), other.true_computation()) &&
1871 eq_computations(false_computation(), other.false_computation());
1872
1873 // These opcodes are not yet supported.
1874 case HloOpcode::kInfeed:
1875 case HloOpcode::kOutfeed:
1876 case HloOpcode::kSort:
1877 case HloOpcode::kRecv:
1878 case HloOpcode::kRecvDone:
1879 case HloOpcode::kSend:
1880 case HloOpcode::kSendDone:
1881 case HloOpcode::kHostCompute:
1882 return false;
1883 }
1884}
1885
1886bool HloInstruction::IsRank2Transpose() const {
1887 return (opcode_ == HloOpcode::kTranspose) &&
1888 dimensions_ == std::vector<int64>({1, 0}) &&
1889 shape_.dimensions_size() == 2 &&
1890 std::equal(shape_.dimensions().begin(), shape_.dimensions().end(),
1891 operands_[0]->shape_.dimensions().rbegin());
1892}
1893
1894void HloInstruction::RemoveUser(HloInstruction* user) {
1895 auto set_it = user_set_.find(user);
1896 CHECK(set_it != user_set_.end());
1897 user_set_.erase(set_it);
1898 // This is linear in the number of the users, but a vector provides a stable
1899 // iteration order and much faster traversal.
1900 auto vec_it = std::find(users_.begin(), users_.end(), user);
1901 CHECK(vec_it != users_.end());
1902 users_.erase(vec_it);
1903}
1904
1905Status HloInstruction::ReplaceUseWith(HloInstruction* user,
1906 HloInstruction* new_producer) {
1907 TF_RET_CHECK(
1908 ShapeUtil::CompatibleIgnoringFpPrecision(shape(), new_producer->shape()))
1909 << "this shape: " << ShapeUtil::HumanString(shape())
1910 << ", replacement shape: "
1911 << ShapeUtil::HumanString(new_producer->shape());
1912
1913 VLOG(3) << "Replacing uses of " << name() << " in " << user->name()
1914 << " with " << new_producer->name();
1915
1916 RemoveUser(user);
1917
1918 TF_RET_CHECK(
1919 std::count(user->operands_.begin(), user->operands_.end(), this) >= 0);
1920 std::replace(user->operands_.begin(), user->operands_.end(), this,
1921 new_producer);
1922 new_producer->AddUser(user);
1923 return Status::OK();
1924}
1925
1926Status HloInstruction::ReplaceOperandWith(int64 operand_num,
1927 HloInstruction* new_operand) {
1928 TF_RET_CHECK(operand_num >= 0);
1929 TF_RET_CHECK(operand_num < operand_count());
1930 HloInstruction* old_operand = mutable_operand(operand_num);
1931 TF_RET_CHECK(ShapeUtil::CompatibleIgnoringFpPrecision(old_operand->shape(),
1932 new_operand->shape()))
1933 << old_operand->shape().ShortDebugString() << " is not compatible with "
1934 << new_operand->shape().ShortDebugString();
1935 operands_[operand_num] = new_operand;
1936
1937 VLOG(3) << "Replacing operand " << operand_num << " of " << name() << " with "
1938 << new_operand->name() << ", was " << old_operand->name();
1939
1940 if (std::find(operands_.begin(), operands_.end(), old_operand) ==
1941 operands_.end()) {
1942 old_operand->RemoveUser(this);
1943 }
1944 new_operand->AddUser(this);
1945 return Status::OK();
1946}
1947
1948Status HloInstruction::ReplaceAllUsesWith(HloInstruction* new_producer) {
1949 bool new_producer_is_user = false;
1950 for (HloInstruction* user : users()) {
1951 if (user == new_producer) {
1952 // It's possible that new_producer is a user of this instruction as might
1953 // be the case when replacing an instruction with a kCopy of itself. In
1954 // this case, don't do the replacement to avoid creating a cycle in the
1955 // graph. new_producer remains the only user of this instruction.
1956 new_producer_is_user = true;
1957 } else {
1958 std::replace(user->operands_.begin(), user->operands_.end(), this,
1959 new_producer);
1960 new_producer->AddUser(user);
1961 }
1962 }
1963 users_.clear();
1964 user_set_.clear();
1965 if (new_producer_is_user) {
1966 AddUser(new_producer);
1967 }
1968 if (parent_ && parent_->root_instruction() == this) {
1969 parent_->set_root_instruction(new_producer);
1970 }
1971
1972 return Status::OK();
1973}
1974
1975void HloInstruction::DetachFromOperands() {
1976 VLOG(3) << "DetachFromOperands:\n " << ToString();
1977 CHECK_EQ(0, user_count());
1978 // An instruction may be repeated as an operand. To avoid calling RemoveUser
1979 // twice on the same operand, keep a set of already detached operands.
1980 std::set<HloInstruction*> detached_operands;
1981 for (int64 operand_num = 0; operand_num < operand_count(); ++operand_num) {
1982 HloInstruction* operand = operands_[operand_num];
1983 if (!ContainsKey(detached_operands, operand)) {
1984 operand->RemoveUser(this);
1985 detached_operands.insert(operand);
1986 }
1987 operands_[operand_num] = nullptr;
1988 }
1989}
1990
1991HloComputation* HloInstruction::to_apply() const {
1992 switch (opcode_) {
1993 case HloOpcode::kCall:
1994 case HloOpcode::kMap:
1995 case HloOpcode::kReduceWindow:
1996 case HloOpcode::kReduce:
1997 CHECK_EQ(called_computations_.size(), 1);
1998 return called_computations_[0];
1999 default:
2000 LOG(FATAL) << "Invalid opcode for to_apply(): "
2001 << HloOpcodeString(opcode());
2002 }
2003}
2004
2005void HloInstruction::set_to_apply(HloComputation* computation) {
2006 // Don't allow changing the computation for fused instructions so we don't
2007 // have to recompute called_instructions for the entire fusion instruction.
2008 CHECK(!IsFused());
2009 switch (opcode_) {
2010 case HloOpcode::kCall:
2011 case HloOpcode::kMap:
2012 case HloOpcode::kReduceWindow:
2013 case HloOpcode::kReduce:
2014 CHECK_EQ(called_computations_.size(), 1);
2015 called_computations_[0] = computation;
2016 break;
2017 default:
2018 LOG(FATAL) << "Invalid opcode for to_apply(): "
2019 << HloOpcodeString(opcode());
2020 }
2021}

2126
2127string HloInstruction::ToString(const HloPrintOptions& options) const {
2128 string result =
2129 StrCat(PrintName(name(), options), " = ",
2130 ShapeUtil::HumanStringWithLayout(shape()), " ",
2131 HloOpcodeString(opcode()), "(", OperandsToString(options), ")");
2132 for (const string& extra : ExtraAttributesToString(options)) {
2133 StrAppend(&result, ", ", extra);
2134 }
2135 if (options.print_metadata() &&
2136 (!metadata_.op_type().empty() || !metadata_.op_name().empty() ||
2137 !metadata_.source_file().empty())) {
2138 StrAppend(&result, ", metadata={", xla::OpMetadataToString(metadata_), "}");
2139 }
2140 return result;
2141}
2142
2143string HloInstruction::OperandsToString(const HloPrintOptions& options) const {
2144 string operands;
2145 if (opcode() == HloOpcode::kConstant) {
2146 // For constants, show the actual value in place of an empty operand list.
2147 if ((!ShapeUtil::IsTuple(shape()) &&
2148 ShapeUtil::ElementsIn(shape()) <= 10) ||
2149 options.print_large_constants()) {
2150 // Literal::ToString emits multidimensional arrays over multiple
2151 // lines. Compact this into one line by stripping out white space.
2152 string tmp = literal().ToString();
2153 std::replace(tmp.begin(), tmp.end(), '\n', ' ');
2154 std::vector<string> v = tensorflow::str_util::Split(tmp, ' ');
2155 bool first = true;
2156 // Concatenate elements in "v" with spaces separating them, but ignoring
2157 // empty entries.
2158 for (const auto& s : v) {
2159 if (s.empty()) {
2160 continue;
2161 }
2162 StrAppend(&operands, (first ? "" : " "), s);
2163 first = false;
2164 }
2165 } else {
2166 // Do not show large constants or tuples.
2167 operands = "{...}";
2168 }
2169 } else if (opcode() == HloOpcode::kParameter) {
2170 StrAppend(&operands, parameter_number_);
2171 } else {
2172 tensorflow::gtl::ArraySlice<HloInstruction*> slice(operands_);
2173 const int64 kMaxOperandsToShowIfCompact = 4;
2174 if (options.compact_operands() &&
2175 slice.size() > kMaxOperandsToShowIfCompact) {
2176 slice.remove_suffix(slice.size() - kMaxOperandsToShowIfCompact);
2177 }
2178 operands = Join(slice, ", ", [&](string* out, HloInstruction* operand) {
2179 std::vector<string> str;
2180 if (options.print_operand_shape()) {
2181 str.push_back(ShapeUtil::HumanStringWithLayout(operand->shape()));
2182 }
2183 if (!options.compact_operands()) {
2184 str.push_back(PrintName(operand->name(), options));
2185 }
2186 StrAppend(out, Join(str, " "));
2187 });
2188 const int64 remaining = operands_.size() - slice.size();
2189 if (slice.size() != operands_.size()) {
2190 StrAppend(&operands, ", ...(+", remaining, ")");
2191 }
2192 }
2193 return operands;
2194}
2195
2196std::vector<string> HloInstruction::ExtraAttributesToString(
2197 const HloPrintOptions& options) const {
2198 std::vector<string> extra;
2199 if (opcode() == HloOpcode::kFusion) {
2200 extra.push_back(StrCat("kind=", xla::ToString(fusion_kind())));
2201 }
2202 if (CanHaveDimensionsField()) {
2203 extra.push_back(StrCat("dimensions={", Join(dimensions(), ","), "}"));
2204 }
2205 if (window_ != nullptr && window_->dimensions_size() != 0) {
2206 extra.push_back(StrCat("window={", window_util::ToString(*window_), "}"));
2207 }
2208 if (padding_config_ != nullptr) {
2209 extra.push_back(
2210 StrCat("padding=", xla::PaddingConfigToString(*padding_config_)));
2211 }
2212 if (opcode() == HloOpcode::kSlice) {
2213 std::vector<string> bounds;
2214 bounds.reserve(slice_starts_.size());
2215 const bool omit_stride =
2216 std::all_of(slice_strides_.begin(), slice_strides_.end(),
2217 [](int64 stride) { return stride == 1; });
2218 for (int i = 0; i < slice_starts_.size(); ++i) {
2219 string stride_str = omit_stride ? "" : StrCat(":", slice_strides_[i]);
2220 bounds.push_back(StrCat("[", slice_starts_[i], ":", slice_limits_[i],
2221 stride_str, "]"));
2222 }
2223 extra.push_back(StrCat("slice={", Join(bounds, ", "), "}"));
2224 }
2225 if (opcode() == HloOpcode::kDynamicSlice) {
2226 extra.push_back(
2227 StrCat("dynamic_slice_sizes={", Join(dynamic_slice_sizes(), ","), "}"));
2228 }
2229 if (opcode() == HloOpcode::kBatchNormTraining ||
2230 opcode() == HloOpcode::kBatchNormInference ||
2231 opcode() == HloOpcode::kBatchNormGrad) {
2232 extra.push_back(StrCat("epsilon=", epsilon()));
2233 extra.push_back(StrCat("feature_index=", feature_index()));
2234 }
2235
2236 if (convolution_dimension_numbers_ != nullptr) {
2237 extra.push_back(ConvolutionDimensionNumbersToString());
2238 }
2239 if (dot_dimension_numbers_ != nullptr) {
2240 extra.push_back(DotDimensionNumbersToString());
2241 }
2242 if (gather_dimension_numbers_ != nullptr) {
2243 extra.push_back(GatherDimensionNumbersToString());
2244 extra.push_back(
2245 StrCat("window_bounds={", Join(gather_window_bounds(), ","), "}"));
2246 }
2247 if (opcode() == HloOpcode::kFft) {
2248 extra.push_back(StrCat("fft_type=", FftType_Name(fft_type())));
2249 extra.push_back(StrCat("fft_length={", Join(fft_length(), ","), "}"));
2250 }
2251
2252 if (options.print_subcomputation_references()) {
2253 if (opcode() == HloOpcode::kWhile) {
2254 extra.push_back(
2255 StrCat("condition=", PrintName(while_condition()->name(), options)));
2256 extra.push_back(
2257 StrCat("body=", PrintName(while_body()->name(), options)));
2258 } else if (opcode() == HloOpcode::kSelectAndScatter) {
2259 extra.push_back(StrCat("select=", PrintName(select()->name(), options)));
2260 extra.push_back(
2261 StrCat("scatter=", PrintName(scatter()->name(), options)));
2262 } else if (opcode() == HloOpcode::kConditional) {
2263 extra.push_back(StrCat("true_computation=",
2264 PrintName(true_computation()->name(), options)));
2265 extra.push_back(StrCat("false_computation=",
2266 PrintName(false_computation()->name(), options)));
2267 } else if (opcode() == HloOpcode::kCall || opcode() == HloOpcode::kMap ||
2268 opcode() == HloOpcode::kReduceWindow ||
2269 opcode() == HloOpcode::kReduce) {
2270 extra.push_back(
2271 StrCat("to_apply=", PrintName(to_apply()->name(), options)));
2272 } else if (!called_computations().empty()) {
2273 extra.push_back(StrCat(
2274 "calls=", Join(called_computations(), ", ",
2275 [&](string* out, const HloComputation* computation) {
2276 StrAppend(out,
2277 PrintName(computation->name(), options));
2278 })));
2279 }
2280 }
2281
2282 if (opcode() == HloOpcode::kSend || opcode() == HloOpcode::kRecv ||
2283 opcode() == HloOpcode::kSendDone || opcode() == HloOpcode::kRecvDone) {
2284 extra.push_back(StrCat("channel_id=", channel_id_));
2285 }
2286
2287 if (opcode() == HloOpcode::kGetTupleElement) {
2288 extra.push_back(StrCat("index=", tuple_index()));
2289 }
2290 if (has_sharding()) {
2291 extra.push_back(StrCat("sharding=", sharding().ToString()));
2292 }
2293 if (!control_predecessors_.empty()) {
2294 extra.push_back(StrCat("control-predecessors={",
2295 Join(control_predecessors_, ", ",
2296 [&](string* out, HloInstruction* pre) {
2297 StrAppend(out,
2298 PrintName(pre->name(), options));
2299 }),
2300 "}"));
2301 }
2302 if (opcode() == HloOpcode::kInfeed && !infeed_config_.empty()) {
2303 extra.push_back(StrCat("infeed_config=\"", CEscape(infeed_config_), "\""));
2304 }
2305 if (opcode() == HloOpcode::kOutfeed && !outfeed_config_.empty()) {
2306 extra.push_back(
2307 StrCat("outfeed_config=\"", CEscape(outfeed_config_), "\""));
2308 }
2309 if (opcode() == HloOpcode::kRng) {
2310 extra.push_back(
2311 StrCat("distribution=", RandomDistributionToString(distribution_)));
2312 }
2313 if (opcode() == HloOpcode::kReducePrecision) {
2314 extra.push_back(StrCat("exponent_bits=", exponent_bits_));
2315 extra.push_back(StrCat("mantissa_bits=", mantissa_bits_));
2316 }
2317

2319 // !options.print_subcomputation_references(), because the call target is not
2320 // an HloComputation.
2321 if (opcode() == HloOpcode::kCustomCall) {
2322 extra.push_back(
2323 StrCat("custom_call_target=\"", CEscape(custom_call_target_), "\""));
2324 }
2325 return extra;
2326}

2337HloInstructionProto HloInstruction::ToProto() const {
2338 HloInstructionProto proto;
2339 CHECK(unique_id_ != -1)
2340 << "This instruction does not have a valid id. Please make sure the "
2341 "instruction is inside a module before dumping it.";
2342 proto.set_id(unique_id_);
2343 proto.set_name(name_);
2344 proto.set_opcode(HloOpcodeString(opcode_));
2345 *proto.mutable_shape() = shape_;

2347 proto.add_operand_ids(operand->unique_id());
2348 }
2349 for (const HloInstruction* control : control_predecessors_) {
2350 proto.add_control_predecessor_ids(control->unique_id());
2351 }
2352
2353 *proto.mutable_metadata() = metadata_;
2354 if (literal_ != nullptr) {
2355 *proto.mutable_literal() = literal_->ToProto();
2356 }
2357 proto.set_parameter_number(parameter_number_);

2360 proto.add_called_computation_ids(

2362 } else {
2363 for (const HloComputation* computation : called_computations_) {
2364 proto.add_called_computation_ids(computation->unique_id());
2365 }
2366 }
2367
2368 proto.set_tuple_index(tuple_index_);
2369 for (int64 dimension : dimensions_) {
2370 proto.add_dimensions(dimension);
2371 }
2372 if (window_ != nullptr) {
2373 *proto.mutable_window() = *window_;
2374 }
2375 if (convolution_dimension_numbers_ != nullptr) {
2376 *proto.mutable_convolution_dimension_numbers() =

2378 }

2380 *proto.mutable_dot_dimension_numbers() = *dot_dimension_numbers_;
2381 }

2400 }
2401 if (padding_config_ != nullptr) {

2403 }
2404 proto.set_outfeed_config(outfeed_config_);
2405 if (opcode() == HloOpcode::kRng) {

2407 }

2422string HloInstruction::ToCategory() const {
2423 if (opcode() == HloOpcode::kTranspose || opcode() == HloOpcode::kCopy ||
2424 opcode() == HloOpcode::kReshape) {
2425 return "data formatting";
2426 }
2427
2428 if (opcode() == HloOpcode::kConvolution) {
2429 string category = "convolution";
2430 if (window_util::HasBaseDilation(window())) {
2431 category += " base-dilated";
2432 }
2433 if (window_util::HasWindowDilation(window())) {
2434 category += " window-dilated";
2435 }
2436 return category;
2437 }
2438
2439 // Give transpose-dot and backwards-conv fusions the categories "dot" and
2440 // "convolution" so they match the categories of proper kDot and kConvolution
2441 // ops. These fusion categories are really just a way of expressing a
2442 // particular kind of dot or conv, so they should have the same category as a
2443 // vanilla dot/conv.
2444 if (opcode() == HloOpcode::kFusion) {
2445 switch (fusion_kind()) {
2446 case FusionKind::kLoop:
2447 return "loop fusion";
2448 case FusionKind::kInput:
2449 return "input fusion";
2450 case FusionKind::kOutput:
2451 return "output fusion";
2452 case FusionKind::kTransposeDot:
2453 return "dot";
2454 case FusionKind::kCustom:
2455 return "custom fusion";
2456 }
2457 }
2458
2459 if (IsElementwise()) {
2460 return "non-fusion elementwise";
2461 }
2462
2463 return HloOpcodeString(opcode());
2464}

2725using DFSStack =
2726 tensorflow::gtl::InlinedVector<std::pair<int, HloInstruction*>, 16>;
2727
2728// Push "child" onto the dfs_stack if not already visited. Returns false if a
2729// cycle was detected, and true otherwise.
2730template <typename Visitor>
2731inline bool PushDFSChild(Visitor* visitor, DFSStack* dfs_stack,
2732 HloInstruction* child) {
2733 CHECK(child != nullptr);
2734 const int id = child->unique_id();
2735 CHECK_GE(id, 0) << "instruction may not have a parent computation";
2736 switch (visitor->GetVisitState(id)) {
2737 case Visitor::kVisiting:
2738 return false;
2739
2740 case Visitor::kVisited:
2741 // Nothing to do
2742 return true;
2743
2744 case Visitor::kNotVisited:
2745 dfs_stack->push_back(std::make_pair(id, child));
2746 return true;
2747 }
2748}
2749
2750using InternalCompareFunction =
2751 std::function<bool(std::pair<int, const HloInstruction*>,
2752 std::pair<int, const HloInstruction*>)>;
2753template <typename Visitor>
2754static Status PostOrderDFS(HloInstruction* root, Visitor* visitor,
2755 const InternalCompareFunction* operand_order,
2756 bool ignore_control_predecessors) {
2757 visitor->ReserveVisitStates(root->GetModule()->NumUniqueInstructionIds());
2758
2759 // dfs_stack holds pairs of <HloInstruction*->unique_id(), HloInstruction*>.
2760 //
2761 // We need to keep track of both the id and the instruction because
2762 // instructions can get deleted while they are on the stack, so we
2763 // can't always use the (potentially dead) instruction object to grab
2764 // its id.
2765 DFSStack dfs_stack;
2766 dfs_stack.emplace_back(root->unique_id(), root);
2767
2768 do {
2769 DCHECK(!dfs_stack.empty());
2770
2771 int current_id = dfs_stack.back().first;
2772 HloInstruction* current_node = dfs_stack.back().second;
2773 CHECK_GE(current_id, 0) << current_id << ": " << current_node
2774 << ": instruction may not have parent computation";
2775 typename Visitor::VisitState visit_state =
2776 visitor->GetVisitState(current_id);
2777 if (visit_state == Visitor::kVisited) {
2778 dfs_stack.pop_back();
2779 VLOG(3) << "Not visiting HLO %" << current_node->name()
2780 << " as it was already visited.";
2781 continue;
2782 }
2783
2784 if (visit_state == Visitor::kVisiting) {
2785 dfs_stack.pop_back();
2786
2787 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(visitor->Preprocess(current_node));
2788 VLOG(2) << "Visiting HLO %" << current_node->name();
2789 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(current_node->Visit(visitor));
2790 visitor->SetVisitState(current_id, Visitor::kVisited);
2791 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(visitor->Postprocess(current_node));
2792 continue;
2793 }
2794
2795 visitor->SetVisitState(current_id, Visitor::kVisiting);
2796
2797 const size_t old_dfs_stack_size = dfs_stack.size();
2798 for (HloInstruction* child : current_node->operands()) {
2799 if (!TF_PREDICT_TRUE(PushDFSChild(visitor, &dfs_stack, child))) {
2800 return FailedPrecondition(
2801 "A cycle is detected while visiting instruction %s",
2802 current_node->ToString().c_str());
2803 }
2804 }
2805
2806 if (!ignore_control_predecessors) {
2807 for (HloInstruction* child : current_node->control_predecessors()) {
2808 if (!TF_PREDICT_TRUE(PushDFSChild(visitor, &dfs_stack, child))) {
2809 return FailedPrecondition(
2810 "A cycle is detected while visiting instruction %s",
2811 current_node->ToString().c_str());
2812 }
2813 }
2814 }
2815
2816 if (operand_order != nullptr) {
2817 std::sort(dfs_stack.begin() + old_dfs_stack_size, dfs_stack.end(),
2818 *operand_order);
2819 }
2820
2821 // This makes the traversal order the same as what you'd expect
2822 // out of a recursive algorithm.
2823 std::reverse(dfs_stack.begin() + old_dfs_stack_size, dfs_stack.end());
2824 } while (!dfs_stack.empty());
2825
2826 return Status::OK();
2827}
2828
2829template <typename HloInstructionPtr>
2830Status HloInstruction::Accept(DfsHloVisitorBase<HloInstructionPtr>* visitor,
2831 bool call_finish_visit,
2832 bool ignore_control_predecessors) {
2833 VLOG(3) << "HloInstruction::Accept(%" << name() << ")";
2834 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(
2835 PostOrderDFS(this, visitor, nullptr, ignore_control_predecessors));
2836 if (call_finish_visit) {
2837 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(visitor->FinishVisit(this));
2838 }
2839 return Status::OK();
2840}

2842// Explicit instantiations.
2843template Status HloInstruction::Accept(DfsHloVisitor*, bool, bool);
2844template Status HloInstruction::Accept(ConstDfsHloVisitor*, bool, bool);
2845
2846Status HloInstruction::AcceptWithOperandOrder(
2847 DfsHloVisitor* visitor, const CompareFunction& operand_order,
2848 bool call_finish_visit) {
2849 VLOG(2) << "HloInstruction::AcceptWithOperandOrder(%" << name() << ")";
2850 InternalCompareFunction func = [&operand_order](
2851 std::pair<int, const HloInstruction*> a,
2852 std::pair<int, const HloInstruction*> b) {
2853 // Call the client's comparison function on the actual HloInstruction*
2854 // objects (ignoring the internal ids we also have in our stack entries)
2855 return operand_order(a.second, b.second);
2856 };
2857 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(PostOrderDFS(this, visitor, &func,
2858 /*ignore_control_predecessors=*/false));
2859 if (call_finish_visit) {
2860 VLOG(3) << "HloInstruction::AcceptWithOperandOrder BEFORE FINISH VISIT";
2861 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(visitor->FinishVisit(this));
2862 VLOG(3) << "HloInstruction::AcceptWithOperandOrder AFTER FINISH VISIT";
2863 }
2864 VLOG(2) << "HloInstruction::AcceptWithOperandOrder EXIT";
2865 return Status::OK();
2866}

2870// Returns true if the given order is a topological sort of the instructions
2871// it contains.
2872bool OrderIsTopologicalSort(const std::vector<const HloInstruction*>& order) {
2873 // Create a map from instruction to its position in 'order'.
2874 std::unordered_map<const HloInstruction*, int> order_position;
2875 for (int i = 0; i < order.size(); i++) {
2876 if (!order_position.insert({order[i], i}).second) {
2877 // Instruction order[i] is duplicated in the order.
2878 return false;
2879 }
2880 }
2881 // Verify that the operand of each instruction in the order is also in the
2882 // order *and* the operand's position is earlier (defs are before uses for
2883 // all ops).
2884 for (auto* instruction : order) {
2885 for (auto* operand : instruction->operands()) {
2886 if (!ContainsKey(order_position, operand) ||
2887 order_position.at(operand) >= order_position.at(instruction)) {
2888 return false;
2889 }
2890 }
2891 }
2892
2893 return true;
2894}

2909
2910Status HloInstruction::AcceptOrdered(
2911 DfsHloVisitor* visitor, const std::vector<const HloInstruction*>& order) {
2912 VLOG(2) << "HloInstruction::AcceptOrdered(%" << name() << ")";
2913 TF_RET_CHECK(OrderIsTopologicalSort(order));
2914
2915 // Compute the predecessors of this instruction.
2916 std::unordered_set<const HloInstruction*> predecessors;
2917 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(this->Accept([&predecessors](HloInstruction* instruction) {
2918 predecessors.insert(instruction);
2919 return Status::OK();
2920 }));
2921
2922 for (auto* const_instruction : order) {
2923 if (!ContainsKey(predecessors, const_instruction)) {
2924 // Instruction is not a predecessors of 'this'.
2925 continue;
2926 }
2927
2928 // The visitor can mark instructions as visited to skip particular
2929 // instructions.
2930 if (visitor->DidVisit(*const_instruction)) {
2931 VLOG(3) << "Not visiting HLO %" << const_instruction->name()
2932 << " as it was already visited.";
2933 continue;
2934 }
2935
2936 HloInstruction* instruction =
2937 const_cast<HloInstruction*>(const_instruction);
2938
2939 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(visitor->Preprocess(instruction));
2940 VLOG(2) << "Visiting HLO %" << instruction->name();
2941 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(instruction->Visit(visitor));
2942 visitor->SetVisited(*instruction);
2943 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(visitor->Postprocess(instruction));
2944 }
2945
2946 return visitor->FinishVisit(this);
2947}
