2975bool HloInstruction::IsElementwise() const {
2976 switch (opcode_) {
2977 // Nullary elementwise operations.
2978 case HloOpcode::kConstant:
2979 return true;
2980
2981 // Unary elementwise operations.
2982 case HloOpcode::kAbs:
2983 case HloOpcode::kRoundNearestAfz:
2984 case HloOpcode::kCeil:
2985 case HloOpcode::kConvert:
2986 case HloOpcode::kBitcastConvert:
2987 case HloOpcode::kCopy:
2988 case HloOpcode::kCos:
2989 case HloOpcode::kExp:
2990 case HloOpcode::kFloor:
2991 case HloOpcode::kImag:
2992 case HloOpcode::kIsFinite:
2993 case HloOpcode::kLog:
2994 case HloOpcode::kNot:
2995 case HloOpcode::kNegate:
2996 case HloOpcode::kReal:
2997 case HloOpcode::kReducePrecision:
2998 case HloOpcode::kSign:
2999 case HloOpcode::kSin:
3000 case HloOpcode::kTanh:
3001 CHECK_EQ(1, operand_count());
3002 return true;
3003
3004 // Binary elementwise operations, the same as in IsElementwiseBinary().
3005 case HloOpcode::kAdd:
3006 case HloOpcode::kAtan2:
3007 case HloOpcode::kComplex:
3008 case HloOpcode::kDivide:
3009 case HloOpcode::kEq:
3010 case HloOpcode::kGe:
3011 case HloOpcode::kGt:
3012 case HloOpcode::kLe:
3013 case HloOpcode::kLt:
3014 case HloOpcode::kMaximum:
3015 case HloOpcode::kMinimum:
3016 case HloOpcode::kMultiply:
3017 case HloOpcode::kNe:
3018 case HloOpcode::kPower:
3019 case HloOpcode::kRemainder:
3020 case HloOpcode::kSubtract:
3021 case HloOpcode::kAnd:
3022 case HloOpcode::kOr:
3023 case HloOpcode::kShiftLeft:
3024 case HloOpcode::kShiftRightArithmetic:
3025 case HloOpcode::kShiftRightLogical:
3026 CHECK_EQ(2, operand_count());
3027 return true;
3028
3029 // Ternary elementwise operations.
3030 case HloOpcode::kSelect:
3031 return !ShapeUtil::IsTuple(shape_);
3032 case HloOpcode::kClamp:
3033 return true;
3034
3035 // Other operations.
3036 case HloOpcode::kRng:
3037 case HloOpcode::kMap:
3038 return true;
3039 case HloOpcode::kFusion:
3040 if (fusion_kind() != FusionKind::kLoop) {
3041 return false;
3042 }
3043 for (auto* fused : fused_instructions()) {
3044 if (fused->opcode() != HloOpcode::kParameter &&
3045 !fused->IsElementwise()) {
3046 return false;
3047 }
3048 }
3049 return true;
3050
3051 default:
3052 return false;
3053 }
3054}

3062bool IsInstructionElementwiseOnOperand(const HloInstruction* instruction,
3063 const HloInstruction* operand) {

3065 return std::all_of(

3069 });

3072
3073bool HloInstruction::IsElementwiseOnOperand(int64 operand_idx) const {
3074 // For all instructions other than kFusion, being elementwise on one of the
3075 // operands is equivalent to being elementwise on all the operands.
3076 if (opcode() != HloOpcode::kFusion) {
3077 return IsElementwise();
3078 }
3079
3080 CHECK_EQ(HloOpcode::kFusion, opcode());
3081 if (fusion_kind() != FusionKind::kLoop) {
3082 return false;
3083 }
3084
3085 // A loop-fusion is elementwise on an operand if all operations (computed
3086 // using BFS) between the operand and the fused root are elementwise.
3087 std::deque<HloInstruction*> worklist;
3088 std::unordered_set<const HloInstruction*> visited;
3089 worklist.push_back(fused_parameter(operand_idx));
3090 visited.insert(fused_parameter(operand_idx));
3091 while (!worklist.empty()) {
3092 HloInstruction* operand = worklist.front();
3093 worklist.pop_front();
3094 for (HloInstruction* user : operand->users()) {
3095 CHECK_GE(user->unique_id(), 0);
3096 if (ContainsKey(visited, user)) {
3097 continue;
3098 }
3099 if (user->IsElementwise() ||
3100 IsInstructionElementwiseOnOperand(user, operand)) {
3101 worklist.push_back(user);
3102 visited.insert(user);
3103 } else {
3104 return false;
3105 }
3106 }
3107 }
3108 return true;
3109}
3110
3111// A helper class for memoized, recursive computation of HloOpcode::kFusion
3112// in HloInstruction::OperandElementUse below.
3113class HloInstruction::FusionReusesParamElements {
3114 public:
3115 using UseKind = HloInstruction::UseKind;
3116
3117 // We could rather iterate backwards through fused_instructions_ here, as it
3118 // is in reverse postorder, and compute whether each fused instruction reuses
3119 // the value of this parameter, which would save stack space but not allow us
3120 // to finish early if we find a reuse.
3121 static UseKind Compute(int64 i, const HloInstruction& hlo) {
3122 tensorflow::gtl::FlatMap<const HloInstruction*, UseKind> memoization_cache;
3123 return ComputeInternal(i, hlo, &memoization_cache);
3124 }
3125
3126 private:
3127 static UseKind ComputeInternal(
3128 int64 i, const HloInstruction& hlo,
3129 tensorflow::gtl::FlatMap<const HloInstruction*, UseKind>* cache) {
3130 if (hlo.opcode_ == HloOpcode::kParameter && hlo.parameter_number_ == i) {
3131 return UseKind::kUse;
3132 }
3133
3134 auto p = cache->emplace(&hlo, UseKind{});
3135 auto value_it = p.first;
3136 const bool key_is_new = p.second;
3137
3138 if (key_is_new) {
3139 for (int64 j = 0; j < hlo.operands_.size(); ++j) {
3140 UseKind old_val = value_it->second;
3141
3142 // The next operation invalidates iterators.
3143 UseKind new_val =
3144 Plus(old_val, std::min(hlo.OperandElementUse(j),
3145 ComputeInternal(i, *hlo.operand(j), cache)));
3146
3147 // Re-acquire the iterator. We could work harder to do this only if
3148 // absolutely necessary, but this code is not hot enough to warrant
3149 // that.
3150 value_it = cache->find(&hlo);
3151 value_it->second = new_val;
3152 }
3153 }
3154 return value_it->second;
3155 }
3156
3157 // Fold operation for UseKinds.
3158 static UseKind Plus(UseKind a, UseKind b) {
3159 if (a == UseKind::kNoUse) {
3160 return b;
3161 } else if (b == UseKind::kNoUse) {
3162 return a;
3163 } else if (a == UseKind::kReuse || b == UseKind::kReuse) {
3164 return UseKind::kReuse;
3165 } else if (a == UseKind::kUsePermutingElements ||
3166 b == UseKind::kUsePermutingElements) {
3167 return UseKind::kReuse;
3168 } else {
3169 CHECK(a == UseKind::kUse && b == UseKind::kUse);
3170 return UseKind::kUse;
3171 }
3172 }
3173};
3174
3175HloInstruction::UseKind HloInstruction::OperandElementUse(int64 i) const {
3176 switch (opcode_) {
3177 case HloOpcode::kBitcast:
3178 case HloOpcode::kConcatenate:
3179 case HloOpcode::kReshape:
3180 case HloOpcode::kReverse:
3181 case HloOpcode::kSlice:
3182 case HloOpcode::kTranspose:
3183 return UseKind::kUsePermutingElements;
3184 case HloOpcode::kPad:
3185 case HloOpcode::kReduce:
3186 // Pad reuses the padding value but not the padded array elements.
3187 // Reduce reuses the init value but not the operand array elements.
3188 return i > 0 ? UseKind::kReuse : UseKind::kUsePermutingElements;
3189 case HloOpcode::kFusion:
3190 // Uses the memoizing, recursive computation defined above.
3191 return FusionReusesParamElements::Compute(i, *fused_expression_root());
3192 case HloOpcode::kDot:
3193 // Dot operations with inputs [A,B] * [B,1] do not re-use
3194 // elements on their left operand.
3195 // Dot operations with inputs [1,A] * [A,B] do not re-use
3196 // elements on their right operand.
3197 if (shape().dimensions_size() == 2) {
3198 if ((i == 0 && shape().dimensions(1) == 1) ||
3199 (i == 1 && shape().dimensions(0) == 1)) {
3200 return UseKind::kUse;
3201 }
3202 }
3203 return UseKind::kReuse;
3204 case HloOpcode::kDynamicUpdateSlice:
3205 // Dynamic-update-slice reuses only operand 2 (start_indices).
3206 if (i == 0 || i == 1) {
3207 return UseKind::kUse;
3208 }
3209 return UseKind::kReuse;
3210 default:
3211 return IsElementwise() && !ImplicitlyBroadcastsOperand(i)
3212 ? UseKind::kUse
3213 : UseKind::kReuse;
3214 }
3215}

3223 shape_);

3320string HloInstruction::ConvolutionDimensionNumbersToString() const {
3321 string result;
3322 if (convolution_dimension_numbers_ == nullptr) {
3323 return result;
3324 }
3325 const ConvolutionDimensionNumbers& dnums = *convolution_dimension_numbers_;
3326 // Show the given dimension labels in order of major to minor based on the
3327 // shape's layout.
3328 const auto append_dims = [&](const std::vector<string>& dims,
3329 const Shape& shape) {
3330 CHECK_EQ(dims.size(), ShapeUtil::Rank(shape));
3331 StrAppend(&result, Join(dims, ""));
3332 };
3333
3334 // lhs_dims[i] is the symbol of the logical dimension i for the lhs
3335 // operand. E.g. if batch has dimension number 2, then lhs_dims[2] == "b".
3336 std::vector<string> lhs_dims(2 + dnums.input_spatial_dimensions().size());
3337 lhs_dims[dnums.input_batch_dimension()] = 'b';
3338 lhs_dims[dnums.input_feature_dimension()] = 'f';
3339 for (int64 i = 0; i < dnums.input_spatial_dimensions().size(); ++i) {
3340 lhs_dims[dnums.input_spatial_dimensions(i)] = StrCat(i);
3341 }
3342
3343 std::vector<string> rhs_dims(2 + dnums.kernel_spatial_dimensions().size());
3344 rhs_dims[dnums.kernel_input_feature_dimension()] = "i";
3345 rhs_dims[dnums.kernel_output_feature_dimension()] = "o";
3346 for (int64 i = 0; i < dnums.kernel_spatial_dimensions().size(); ++i) {
3347 rhs_dims[dnums.kernel_spatial_dimensions(i)] = StrCat(i);
3348 }
3349
3350 std::vector<string> output_dims(2 + dnums.output_spatial_dimensions().size());
3351 output_dims[dnums.output_batch_dimension()] = 'b';
3352 output_dims[dnums.output_feature_dimension()] = 'f';
3353 for (int64 i = 0; i < dnums.output_spatial_dimensions().size(); ++i) {
3354 output_dims[dnums.output_spatial_dimensions(i)] = StrCat(i);
3355 }
3356
3357 result += "dim_labels=";
3358 append_dims(lhs_dims, operand(0)->shape());
3359 result += "_";
3360 append_dims(rhs_dims, operand(1)->shape());
3361 result += "->";
3362
3363 // A convolution can be represented as a kConvolution HLO or as a CustomCall
3364 // that returns a tuple, the first element of which is the result of the
3365 // convolution.
3366 Shape this_shape =
3367 ShapeUtil::IsTuple(shape()) ? shape().tuple_shapes(0) : shape();
3368 append_dims(output_dims, this_shape);
3369 return result;
3370}

3443void HloInstruction::RelayoutConstant(const Layout& new_layout,
3444 const ShapeIndex& shape_index) {
